    "body": "When trying to install py-scipy, I get an error message. Should we make the +shared variant of netlib-lapack enabled by default?\n\n``` bash\n$ spack install py-scipy\n==> Error: Invalid spec: 'netlib-lapack@3.5.0%gcc@5.3.0~shared=linux-x86_64^cmake@3.4.0%gcc@5.3.0+ncurses=linux-x86_64^ncurses@6.0%gcc@5.3.0=linux-x86_64^netlib-blas@3.5.0%gcc@5.3.0~fpic=linux-x86_64'. Package netlib-lapack requires variant +shared, but spec asked for ~shared\n```\n",
